ong, a humble bard and musical messenger of Tunare.  Please come in and relax.&quot;  Trevian looks about the room and sees the spirit gems about the walls glowing a soft blue.  &quot;I can tell you are of a good heart.  The spirits of our ancestors are at peace with your presence.<br>
<br>
I can tell you it's been centuries since I've been of your season, but I remember it like it was yesterday.  Battling the orcs back from the Greater Faydark, freeing the slaves held captive there.  Hmm... there are few greater things a Fier'dal holds more dear than freedom, and few deeds more heinous than the bonds of slavery.  The battle for our freedom continues and stretches from the caverns within Crushbone to the distant shores of the Firiona Vie Outpost and beyond.  Many a great tale has been told, and many a new tale that you'll live, I'm certain.<br>
<br>
But enough of this bards ramblings, let me pour you a drink.&quot;  With that he produces a bottle of elven wine and fills a few glasses. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=169421" target="top">Trevian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
