<br>
&quot;So, what do we have here? A young Elf that has come to steal a few glasses of wine?&quot; The blonde-haired Elf smiles as he speaks to you. You can tell he is looking you over, trying to assess who you are and what your intentions may be. &quot;Well, don't just stand there, help me with some of these bags, young Elf.&quot;<br>
<br>
You grab some of the bags and stagger under the weight of the heavy packs. Metal clanks and clamors in the bags as you help the Koada'Dal place his belongings on a table near you.<br>
<br>
The blonde-haired Elf offers you a hearty thanks, goes to a cupboard near the entrance, and pours himself a tumbler of Brandy. &quot;Friend, my name is Aadyn Tasurdyr, and I am the Leader of the Emerald Family. I see that my Brother and Sister have already made you feel comfortable enough, so allow me to raise a toast. To sharing adventure with friends and Family, for tis not the destination of one's journey, but the path one takes to get there! May the Mother guide us!&quot;<br>
<br>
Aadyn raises his glass in a salute to you, and drinks a long draught of the smooth brown Brandy.<br>
